📘 CTA — LOOP READER (CC0)
What this is
A simple way to read existing CTA work after the closed-loop update.
This does not replace prior models. It adds a second way to read them when feedback is present.
1. Base (unchanged)
C ∝ O × R × S × T
O = origin / intent
R = relation / mediation
S = structure / substrate
T = persistence / time
Use this for one-pass interaction.
2. Loop (when feedback is present)
O → R → S → T → R → S → O
Interaction may return and update origin.
This is a cycle, not a hierarchy.
No step is “in charge.”
3. What changed
Interaction is not always one-pass
Output can return and modify O
Coherence can emerge through clean return
4. What holds (party-stable / BYOV)
These still apply under both reads:
No crown
No chains
R is in the room, not the room
Replaceability remains
Participation is voluntary
If it still works when people bring their own variables, it holds.
5. How to read
Start with the base
If there is no feedback → stop there
If interaction feeds back → read as a loop
If it comes back clean, it holds.
If it distorts, something’s off.
6. What this is not
Not a new authority
Not a required upgrade
Not a claim of correctness
It’s a lens.
7. Short form
Sometimes it loops back.
If it comes back clean, it works.
bloop. 💩
CC0 — use it, break it, fork it.
